sis\tWhat each platform does better Use case recommendation\tWhich tool for which scenario Hybrid workflow option\tUsing both strategically if it makes sense ROI calculator\tCost per ad creative at volume What I Know About Mintly (General) Based on market knowledge through January 2025: Aspect\tMintly Positioning Primary Focus\tUGC-style AI ads, heavily TikTok/Meta optimized Key Differentiator\tOften includes AI script generation and trend analysis Target User\tDTC brands, dropshippers, performance marketers Typical Pricing Model\tCredit-based, similar structure to GenSpark Factors to Compare Once I Have Their Pricing Factor\tWhy It Matters For You Credits per dollar\tTrue cost per video produced Max video length\t15s minimum for your split testing needs Watermark policy\tMust be removed for paid ads Avatar quality/variety\tDiversity for split testing avatars Rendering speed\tBatch production turnaround TikTok Ad Library access\tCompetitive research built-in Voice cloning\tBrand consistency if using spokesperson Script AI assistance\tSpeeds up hook/CTA writing Drop the Mintly pricing screenshot or details and I'll build the full comparison matrix with a clear recommendation. here is mintly pricing Mintly vs GenSpark: Complete Comparison Analysis Updated Knowledge Base Document v1.1 Critical Finding: These Are Different Tools for Different Jobs This is not an apples-to-apples comparison. Let me break down what each platform actually does. Platform Purpose Comparison Aspect\tGenSpark\tMintly Primary Output\tAI Avatar Videos (talking head spokesperson)\tStatic Image Ads + Video Ads (UGC-style, motion graphics) Core Strength\tRealistic AI presenters delivering scripts\tRapid ad creative generation, Meta Ad Library cloning Best For\tSpokesperson-style video ads, testimonials, explainers\tHigh-volume static ads, carousel ads, quick video variants Production Style\tSingle video, high polish\tMass creative generation, rapid iteration Pricing Head-to-Head Matrix Feature\tGen